The paper proposes a novel framework for visual saliency detection using image retrieval techniques. The proposed method involves training a customized SVM from similar example images to predict the saliency values of object proposals in a test image. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and aggregation of regional scores, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on challenging datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
